Maps.MapDescription_Abyss: Abyss was built underground as an unofficial arena away from prying eyes. Eventually, the cost of maintaining a Splitgate arena became too expensive, and it was brought into the official circuit for sponsorship.
Maps.MapDescription_Oasis: As the portal network grew, tourism grew along with it. Oasis is one of many destinations that portal travelers can visit for rest, relaxation, or competition.
Maps.MapDescription_Foregone: Many worship these ancient ruins, left behind by a mysterious civilization. Foregone Destruction’s original purpose is unknown, and identical ruins exist elsewhere on the planet where it was found.
Maps.MapDescription_Silo: Once an underground missile base, Club Silo is now a nightclub where attendees can bet on competitors while safely viewing them from behind bullet-proof glass. Pop singer Audriix is a frequent guest at Club Silo.
Maps.MapDescription_Karman: Sector 3B of the orbital Karman Station is designated as a hangar for incoming and outgoing travelers but is better known for the portal arena beneath.
Maps.MapDescription_Highwind: Situated atop the tallest Japanese forest, this treehouse map is known to be one of the most difficult for portal usage. Many competitors pride themselves on mastering Highwind’s quirks and using it to their advantage.
Maps.MapDescription_Stadium: Splitgate’s first ever competition was played on Stadium, which has maintained itself as the premiere arena for high profile events.
Maps.MapDescription_Helix: The Helix Penal Complex houses some of the most dangerous criminals in the universe. Convicts can buy time off their sentences with victories in Splitgate competitions.
Maps.MapDescription_Lavawell: The Lavawell research facility was originally built to unlock more of the mysteries behind Proelium. In time, priorities changed, research stopped, and the facility was converted into a Splitgate arena.
Maps.MapDescription_Echo: The fifth virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Alpha: The first virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Delta: The fourth virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Impact: The impact site at Silvertree Farms signified the start of a new era, but many of the alien vessel’s secrets remain unsolved...
Maps.MapDescription_Bravo: The second virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Golf: The seventh virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Foxtrot: The sixth virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Olympus: The sky arena of Olympus was strategically located near a major portal network juncture to draw attention to the sport of Splitgate. Travelers often spectate competitions before continuing on their journeys.
Maps.MapDescription_Pantheon: The temple of Pantheon was built to celebrate the discovery of portals. The arena’s spiritual significance was fleeting.  Splitgate competitions are its main purpose today.
Maps.MapDescription_Charlie: The third virtual arena made for Simulated Splitgate, operating through the immersive hypernet protocol.
Maps.MapDescription_Atlantis: The undersea Atlantis was made to stun visitors with a breathtaking view of the ocean. This iconic location quickly became one of the most highly requested sites for a Splitgate arena.
Maps.MapDescription_Crag: This mining facility integrated portal technology to speed up delicate mining operations. After archeological artifacts were found, mining was halted and Crag was turned into a tourist destination.

Tips.ACD16FA44CA1AB51F9EE1F82ED64F97B: <TYPE>SPRAYS</> <DIVIDER>//</> <BOLD>PRESS</> <ACTION NAME="Spray" WIDTH="30" HEIGHT="30" PADDING="0 5 0 0"/> on a wall or a floor to spray your emblem in a match for other players to see.
Tips.Text_8: Don't forget to use your jetpack! Double tap and hold jump to activate it.
Tips.Text_0: EMP grenades don't damage players, but they destroy enemy portals. Press <ACTION NAME="GRENADE" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/> to throw a grenade.
Tips.Text_11: Hold <ACTION NAME="SPRINT" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/> while in the air to gain speed.
Tips.Text_10: If you jump through a portal at high speed, you will come out the other portal at high speed. Use this to get to strategic locations on maps like Highwind and Outpost!
Tips.Text_13: If you see a dead body, walk over to it and try crouching repeatedly. Press <ACTION NAME="CROUCH" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/> to crouch.
Tips.Text_7: Keep an eye out for flashing portals. It means an enemy is on the other side.
Tips.Text_4: Keep an eye out for power weapons around the map. They are much more effective in combat than the weapons you start with.
Tips.Text_14: Looking to be more involved in the community or have feedback about the game? Head to discord.gg/splitgate and come say hi!
Tips.Text_6: Looking to earn more XP? Try completing a challenge or inviting a friend to earn an XP boost!
Tips.Text_9: Press <ACTION NAME="MELEE" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/> to melee enemies you are close to. Melees do at least 50 damage but scale up with your speed.
Tips.Text_5: Struggling with portals? Check out the race courses in the Training section of the Play options.
Tips.Text_2: Stuck at the bottom of the map? Look up and around for a portal wall to get yourself back in the action.
Tips.Text_3: Try looking for a portal wall behind your enemy. If you can teleport behind them, they won't know what hit them!
Tips.Text_15: Want to admire that awesome gun you're carrying? Press <ACTION NAME="INSPECT" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/> to inspect it.
Tips.Text_1: Want to trash talk your enemies in game? Press <ACTION NAME="PTT_PROXIMITY" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/> to use proximity voice chat!
Tips.Text_12: You can emote before, after, and during a match. Press <ACTION NAME="PLAYEMOTE" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="60" STRETCH="FILL" PADDING="0 20 0 0"/>.

TutorialStrings.TutorialStageFinal_00a: Alright, so you beat the tutorial.  Good.
TutorialStrings.TutorialStageFinal_02a: But as you keep playing with portals, you'll learn and invent a lot of creative ways to outshoot and outsmart your opponents.
TutorialStrings.TutorialStageFinal_05a: Nothing to it, but to do it.
TutorialStrings.TutorialStageFinal_01a: That taught you the basics of Splitgate.
TutorialStrings.TutorialStageFinal_03a: We hope you'll enjoy Splitgate as much as we do!
